HEADWORD: Cinerary
<hw>Cin"er*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cinerarius</ets>, fr. <ets>cinis</ets> ashes.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to ashes; containing ashes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cinerary urns</b></col>, <cd>vessels used by the ancients
to preserve the ashes of the dead when burned.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cineration</ent>⟦br⟧
